President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. These include Todd C. Chapman as Ambassador to the Republic of Ecuador, Steven Michael Haro as Assistant Secretary for Legislative and Intergovernmental Affairs at the Department of Commerce, John Kotek as Assistant Secretary for Nuclear Energy at the Department of Energy, Carolyn Lerner as Special Counsel in the Office of Special Counsel, Matthew John Matthews as United States Senior Official for the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) Forum, and Michael J. Missal as Inspector General at the Department of Veterans Affairs. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts, including Pamela K. Anderson and Gebisa Ejeta as members of the Board for International Food and Agricultural Development, Ronald A. Cass, Jonathan Sallet, and Jane Sherburne as members of the Council of the Administrative Conference of the United States, and Bo Thao-Urabe as a member of the President's Commission on Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders. President Obama expressed confidence that these individuals will help tackle the important challenges facing America.